Install Ubuntu:
ISO File
Mount it and boot from it.

sda5 - Ext4 - /boot - 200 MB
sda6 - Ext4 - /home - 53 GB
sda7 - Swap -         4 GB
sda8 - Ext4 - /     - 46 GB

Mouse position change & scroll.
Install Gdebi to install software.

Install gnome-tweaks
Go to Keyboard -> Additional Layout Options
// Alt mapped to ctrl, ctrl mapped to win
Left Alt as Ctrl, Left Ctrl As Win, Left Win as Left Alt

settings -> Keyboard -> View and Customize Shortcuts -> Navigation -> 
switch windows - alt+` 
switch applications keys to alt+tab.
launch terminal - alt + t
search - alt + space

Vscode install - change keys in vscode

Update Terminal Settings

Over amplification volume

Activate Sharing in Settings for screen sharing
Update /etc/gdm3/custom.conf - uncomment wayland=flase
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE

Sudo apt install git
Sudo apt install npm
Sudo apt install xclip
Sudo snap install postman
